==Old English==

===Etymology===
From a pre-Germanic ''*ghəmon-'', related to Latin [[homo]].  Cognate with Old Saxon [[gumo]], Old High German [[gumo]], Old Norse [[gume]], Gothic [[𐌲𐌿𐌼𐌰]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'gu:ma/

===Noun===
'''gūma''' ''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Old English weak declension|weak]] m''

